headline: ADP Just Raised Its Dividend 10% for the 50th Year in a Row
summary: Automatic Data Processing (NASDAQ:ADP) just raised its quarterly dividend by 10%, marking the company’s 50th consecutive year of dividend increases. That puts ADP in Dividend King territory, an elite group of fewer than 50 companies with half a century of uninterrupted dividend growth. For retirees and income investors, this is the kind of track record ... ADP Just Raised Its Dividend 10% for the 50th Year in a Row
